{
  "texts": [
    "IGHD is known to positively correlate with MS4A1 and CD1C and negatively with CD3D.",
    "We found SEDR's denoised values to show stronger expected gene-gene correlations than the raw and the Sprod [44] denoised values (Fig. 3E, F).",
    "SEDR can handle high-resolution spatial transcriptomicsNewly emerging methods such as Stereo-seq [5], PIXEL-Seq [6], and Seq-Scope [9] can achieve submicrometer and thus subcellular resolution.",
    "With continued technology advancement, the spatial resolution and number of cells detected per tissue will significantly improve, producing large datasets with high throughput.",
    "As such, we evaluated SEDR's performance on Stereo-seq and Slide-seq data of mouse olfactory bulb tissues."
  ]
}